11 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
12 Sec. 1. VERMONT COMMUNITY RADIO GRANT PROGRAM
13 (a) Findings. The General Assembly finds that:
14 (1) Vermont’s seven active community radio stations currently serve
15 over 200,000 Vermonters, many in rural and underserved areas.
16 (2) Community radio stations have consistently provided critical
17 information during emergencies, including Tropical Storm Irene, recent severe
18 flooding, and other natural disasters.
