1 (2) The Program shall be administered by the Commissioner of Public
2 Safety or designee in collaboration with the Vermont Association of
3 Broadcasters.
4 (3) Grants shall be allocated as follows:
5 (A) Up to $25,000.00 per station for seven active community radio
6 stations.
7 (B) Up to $10,000.00 per station for three upcoming stations
8 currently under construction.
9 (4) To be eligible for a grant under the Program, an applicant shall:
10 (A) be a nonprofit, noncommercial community radio station licensed
11 in Vermont;
12 (B) demonstrate a history of providing emergency broadcasting
13 services or show the capacity to provide such services upon funding; and
14 (C) submit a detailed implementation plan for the proposed use of
15 grant funding.
16 (d) Report. On or before June 30, 2026, a community radio station that
17 receives a grant under the Program shall provide to the Commissioner of
18 Public Safety a report detailing the:
19 (1) use of grant funds, including itemized expenses;
20 (2) improvements achieved in emergency readiness and operational
21 capacity; and
